<HEADLINE>
Beijing deploys sniffer dogs in passenger train terminals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 10 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Beijing police began on Thursday to take sniffer dogs onto trains
to check baggage at two of the capital's rail terminals.
</P>
<P>
The dogs, which are trained to detect explosives and other
suspicious substances, will also be taken regularly through
luggage warehouses, platforms and outdoor spaces of the Beijing
Railway Station and Beijing West Railway Station.
</P>
<P>
Other measures, including portable and fixed detectors and
detecting doors, have been put into use in the two terminals.
</P>
<P>
The dogs have been patrolling Beijing's subways since January.
</P>
